iler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}, {"id": 630652267, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWw2MzA2NTIyNjc=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-feature-request", "name": "C-feature-request", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: A feature request, i.e: not implemented / a PR."}, {"id": 1282665911, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxMjgyNjY1OTEx", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-const-generics", "name": "A-const-generics", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: const generics (parameters and arguments)"}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 0, "created_at": "2020-12-30T19:40:35Z", "updated_at": "2020-12-30T19:40:35Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "MEMBER", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Currently, users may specify `_` in place of a type: the compiler will then suggest the intended type. This ought to work for consts too, but currently does not (see https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/79557).\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nfn foo<const N: usize, const K: usize>(data: [u32; N]) -> [u32; K] {\r\n    [0; K]\r\n}\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let a = foo::<_, 2>([0, 1, 2]);\r\n}\r\n```\r\nThe difficulty is that the intended use of `_` (as either a type or const) is ambiguous until type checking, so runs into the same problems as #66615 and #77773.", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/80528/reactions", "total_count": 6, "+1": 6, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/80528/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}